fields.description:
When hitting the API@ 
[/rest/branch-permissions/2.0/projects/\{projectKey}/repos/\{repositorySlug}/restrictions|https://developer.atlassian.com/static/rest/stash/3.11.1/stash-branch-permissions-rest.html]

See attachment for branch-permissions.JPG
the response I get back is:
{code}
{
      "id": 72,
      "type": "read-only",
      "matcher": {
        "id": "**/tags",
        "displayId": "**/tags",
        "type": {
          "id": "PATTERN",
          "name": "Pattern"
        },
        "active": true
      }
    }
{code}

when I would have expected me ('wparad') to be somewhere in the response.

Hyperlinks doesn't work in markdowns. I've followed the docs here
https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/STASH035/Markdown+syntax+guide

This is my exact Stash comment:
{code}
I used `getMapAsync` because `getMap` is [deprecated](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/business/mobile/android/reference/com/google/android/m4b/maps/MapView#getMap())
{code}

Which gets rendered as
{code}
I used getMapAsync because getMap is [deprecated](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/business/mobile/android/reference/com/google/android/m4b/maps/MapView#getMap())
{code}

We are running Atlassian Stash v3.5.0 self hosted.

This suggestion is to make the "path" parameter optional for the function [http://example.com/rest/api/1.0/projects/\{projectKey\}/repos/\{repositorySlug\}/pull-requests/\{pullRequestId\}/comments|https://developer.atlassian.com/static/rest/stash/3.11.1/stash-rest.html#idp2850128], since general comments on pull requests aren't anchored to a path, thus you can't get them using this function - currently it's only possible to get comments from files using it.

If you try not setting the "path", the return is:
{noformat}
{"errors":[{"context":null,"message":"The path query parameter is required when retrieving comments.","exceptionName":null}]}
{noformat}
